sql:
SELECT AVG(average_speed) AS avg_speed
FROM ride_types
WHERE type_name = 'Water Ride';

external_knowledge:
- The "crown jewels of the parks" refers to the top-ranked rides; 
- "locations" refers to the park names where these rides are located;
- "average sparkles" is a metaphor for the average ratings of the rides;
- "the number of people who have witnessed their glory" refers to the review count of the rides.
